Wash and dry all produce. Bring @water{3/4%cup} to a boil in a #small pot. Mince @garlic{2}(minced). Mince half the @jalapeño{1}(minced, half with ribs and seeds removed), removing ribs and seeds for less heat. Thinly slice other half. Zest @lime{1} until you have ½ tsp zest, then cut into halves. Pick @mint{1/4%cup}(leaves picked from stems) from stems; discard stems.

Once water is boiling, add @jasmine rice{1/2%cup} to #pot. Cover, lower heat, and reduce to a simmer. Cook until tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. Keep covered until meal is ready.

Carefully cut @sirloin steak{1%12oz} in half parallel to the cutting board to create two thin filets. Place steak, garlic, @soy sauce{1%tbsp}, lime zest, @brown sugar{2%tsp}, minced jalapeño (to taste), and a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tbsp} in a #medium bowl{}. Season generously with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to evenly coat steak in marinade.

Thinly slice @radishes{3}(thinly sliced). Peel @cucumbers{2}, then halve lengthwise. Scoop out seeds with a #spoon, then slice into thin half-moons. Toss radishes, cucumbers, @white wine vinegar{2%tbsp}, @white sugar{1/2%tsp}, and a large pinch salt and pepper in another medium bowl. Set aside to pickle.

Heat a drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tbsp} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add steak, keeping excess marinade in bowl, and cook until browned, ~{2-3%minutes} per side. Remove from pan and let rest a few minutes before thinly slicing against the grain.

In a #small bowl{}, toss mint leaves, jalapeño slices (to taste), a squeeze of lime, and a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{1%tbsp}. Season with salt and pepper. Divide rice between plates, then top with steak. Scatter mint mixture over top and serve with salad to the side.